South Africa recorded its first infant death due to COVID-19 today. The two-day-old child is believed to have contracted the virus from its mother. The infant was born prematurely and reportedly needed a ventilator directly after birth, due to having lung difficulties. A health care worker, as well as an Old Mutual employee in Cape Town, were also reported to have died of the novel coronavirus. The total number of deaths is now at 339, while the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases recorded in South Africa today is a total of 18003. The department of health reports that 18 252 tests were conducted in the last 24 hours. 